http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/andhra-pradesh/Six-killed-in-road-accidents/article13976913.ece

The New Year started on a tragic note with the death of three revellers and three labourers in separate road accidents at different places in the district on the intervening night of Thursday and Friday.According to sources, Banoth Akshay, a B.Ed student of a Bhadrachalam-based college, was fatally knocked down by an unidentified vehicle while he was on his way home on a bike at Polavaram village in Burgampadu mandal on Thursday night. His father, who was riding pillion, suffered grievous head injuries.In another incident, Mallikarjun, 30, of Medar Bazaar in Khammam town, died after being allegedly hit by a speeding motorbike in front of his house on Thursday night. Mallikarjun was bursting firecrackers on the New Yearâ€™s eve when the tragedy struck.A youth of Bayyaram mandal was killed and three others were injured when their car overturned at Dammakkapeta in Manuguru mandal in the small hours of Friday. In a gruesome accident, three construction labourers were killed and another was injured when the autorickshaw in which they were travelling in was hit by a jeep at V M Banjara in Penuballi mandal on Thursday night.